title: A Seamless Phase 1b/2a Double-blind, Randomized, Multiple Dose, Multi-center, Sequential Dose-escalation Study to Assess the Safety, Tolerability, Pharmacokinetics, Pharmacodynamics and Efficacy of TB006 in Patients With Mild to Severe Alzheimer's Disease
description_brief: Part 1 of this study will be conducted to determine the safety, tolerability, and pharmacokinetic (PK) profile of multiple doses of TB006, as well as the maximum tolerated dose of TB006, and to assess the immunogenicity of TB006 (production of anti-TB006 antibody). Part 2 of this study will be conducted to determine the clinical efficacy of TB006 in participants with mild to severe Alzheimer's Disease.

participantFlowModule.preAssignmentDetails: This was a 2-part randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled, multiple ascending dose (MAD) escalation study that evaluated the safety, tolerability, pharmacokinetics (PK), pharmacodynamics (PD) and efficacy of TB006 in participants with Alzheimer's disease (AD).
participantFlowModule.recruitmentDetails: This was a multi-center study conducted at various centers across United States (US).

outcomeMeasures.title: Part 1: Number of Participants With Suicidal Ideation or Suicidal Behavior as Measured Using Columbia Suicide Severity Rating Scale (C-SSRS)
outcomeMeasures.description: The C-SSRS is an interview-based instrument to systematically assess suicidal ideation and suicidal behavior. Number of participants that have an affirmative response to the 5 items for suicidal ideation (1. Wish to be dead, 2. Non-specific active suicidal thoughts, 3. Active suicidal ideation with any methods without intent to act, 4. Active suicidal ideation with some intent to act, without specific plan, 5. Active suicidal ideation with specific plan and intent) and/or to the 5 items for suicidal behavior (1. Preparatory acts or behavior, 2. Aborted attempt, 3. Interrupted attempt, 4. Actual attempt, 5. Completed suicide) were reported. The total score ranges from 0 (no ideation present) to 5 (active suicidal ideation with specific plan and intent); higher scores indicate worse symptoms.

Change from Baseline value was obtained by subtracting Baseline value from post-dose visit value.

explanation_agent: Reason: The investigational agent TB006 is a humanized IgG4 monoclonal antibody that neutralizes Galectin‑3 (Gal‑3). Galectin‑3 is described in the literature as a regulator of microglial activation and a mediator of neuroinflammation and has been linked to amyloid‐associated microglial responses in AD. These properties place the primary biological focus of TB006 in inflammatory/microglial pathways rather than a direct amyloid or tau epitope. citeturn0search1turn0search6

Act: From the trial description and company/summary pages, TB006 is explicitly a monoclonal antibody against Galectin‑3 (TB006 neutralizes Gal‑3). Company and independent summaries (TrueBinding, AlzForum, peer‑reviewed and conference reporting) identify Gal‑3’s role in microglial activation and neuroinflammation and describe TB006’s mechanism as Gal‑3 neutralization with downstream effects on Aβ/tau oligomerization and inflammation. Based on CADRO definitions, the most specific match is F) Inflammation because the target (Gal‑3) is an inflammatory mediator. citeturn0search0turn0search1turn0search6
